\begin_inset Formula $\text{d}F(y|\theta)$
\end_inset

 labeled by an unknown parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in\Theta$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=(\phi,\lambda)^{\top}$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi\in\Phi$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\in\Lambda$
\end_inset

.
 Assume You are interested in learning parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi\in\Phi$
\end_inset

, and You are not interested in learning the unknown parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\in\Lambda$
\end_inset

; but both 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi,\lambda$
\end_inset

 are parts of the statistical model parameterisation.
 The unknown quantity 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\in\Lambda$
\end_inset

 is called 
\bar under
nuisance parameter
